  <p>NPR did a story on the Trump administration’s decision to alter the way it punishes nursing homes. Starting in the second quarter of 2017, officials were more often assessing one-time “per instance” fines, while the Obama administration relied more heavily on fines that were calculated based on the number of days the home was out of compliance. Those “per day” fines tend to be bigger because they compound, NPR reported.</p>
